summary:
41 days without an eating disorder.
I woke up with a heavy weight on my chest again, extremely worried about next semester...
body:
41 days without an eating disorder.

I woke up with a heavy weight on my chest again, extremely worried about next semester (since it’s my final one). All I can think is that in 4 months I’m supposed to have so much figured out, but my anxiety keeps playing devil’s advocate and asking, “Well what if you don’t get in anywhere? What if you can’t find a job? What if they don’t like you? What if *insert any slippery slope fallacy*?”

It’s fair to think ahead, but bruh, obsessing over it is not going to help and it’s not worth the suffering I put myself through. Like man, we find a way through, chill.

I think I’m also a little lonely. Practically every night of winter break someone wanted to hang out. The last few days I was like “alright dude, just chill on your own”. Which was nice, but I think I’m starting to think that it’s not the amount I hung with people, it’s who I actually chilled with. I guess there’s someone that I want to see and I can have as much fun as I want with others but by the time I’m in bed it felt like a lonely day. Ya’ know, I realize that the only reason I put out, “I wanna’ talk” type of posts on here has only ever been directed to a very tiny group of people. Even though it’s out there for all, I’d rather do that and then they can talk to me if they want to rather than me just fucking sending a message like, “Hey, I just really want to talk to you.” That’s a bad thing, isn’t it? But, fuck, I’d rather do that than risk annoying them.

title: Andre Agassi's biography lessons
body:
Andre Agassi’s biography lessons

These passages explain it all.

“I notice something on the faces of fans too. The way they watch me and ask for my autograph, the way they scream as I enter an arena, makes me uncomfortable, but also satisfies something deep inside me, some hidden craving I didn’t know was there. I’m shy—but I like attention. I cringe when fans start dressing like me—but I also dig it.”

“I had time, if I were more…

summary: [question] electrolytes with daily sauna use via /r/Paleo
title: [question] electrolytes with daily sauna use via /r/Paleo
body:
ive been enjoying going to the sauna at my new gym for the past couple of weeks. however, despite meeting the rda for potassium/calcium and supplementing magnesium and taking about 4g-5g sodium per day, im having symptoms of electrolyte deficiency, only when it comes to sleep though. i feel pretty good during the day but i wake up often during the night and my calves twitch/cramp. if youre using the sauna regularly, do you need to up potassium and or sodium past rda? is 4g of sodium enough per day? ive experimented with going higher to 5g but im not sure it makes a difference for me. anyone have personal experience with this?
